.TH "LIGHTNING-WALLET-PRUNE" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-wallet-prune \- remove old closed accounts from the wallet
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning wallet-prune
.RB [ --days
.IR N ]
.RB [ --dry-run ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Deletes closed accounts — and their associated ledger entries — that
have been closed for more than
.I N
days (default 90).  Only accounts with a
.B closed_at
timestamp are eligible; open accounts are never touched.
.PP
With
.B --dry-run
the command reports what would be removed without modifying the database.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"pruned_accounts":N,"pruned_ledger_rows":N}
.fi
or with
.BR --dry-run :
.nf
{"would_prune_accounts":N,"would_prune_ledger_rows":N,"dry_run":true}
.fi
.TP
.B --days N
Age threshold in days (default 90).
.TP
.B --dry-run
Report only; do not modify the database.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-wallet-check (1),
.BR lightning-wallet-backup (1)
